# A TASK (ticket) — a chapter (the title as the node's SELF-VALUE, a keyed description, and a
# positional body of chunks/subtasks) plus planning fields. Its lifecycle STATE is a tag
# application: the `yamlover-annotations` pointer into the dev workflow. Move it across the
# board by changing that one pointer. Spec: ../../../TICKETS.md §1.
!!<*yamlover:$defs:task>
Split the pointer parser into scope + step phases
description: The parser conflates scope detection with step walking; the colon grammar needs them apart.
priority: high
assignee: claude
estimate: 6h
- The current `parsePointer` walks scopes and steps in one pass, so `::`/`:::` edge cases leak into step logic.
- Target a two-phase parse — resolve the scope ladder first, then walk steps — so `SEPARATOR.md` rules live in one place.
